description.plain:
Maty Noyes is a singer-songwriter from Mississippi signed to Lava/Republic Records.

Noyes was signed to Lava Records by CEO Jason Flom in late 2014, when she was just seventeen. Flom “believe[d] strongly that she will be a star” and signed her to his label, noting that her sound was mature beyond her years, much like superstar labelmate Lorde.

Original material that had been previously released independently was wiped from the internet, allowing her to make her major-label debut in August 2015 as a featured artist on The Weeknd’s Beauty Behind The Madness closer “Angel”. Following the track’s release, she released her first solo single, “Charge It To The Game,”. She also appeared on Kygo’s single “Stay”, which became her first charting release.

“In My Mind” was released as the lead single from her debut EP, Noyes Complaint, and is her most successful solo release to date with over 100 million Spotify streams. The full EP was released in October 2016 featuring four additional tracks. “London” and “Say It To My Face” were released as standalone singles in 2017. Noyes released a series of singles in summer 2018 leading up to her second EP, Love Songs From a Lolita, released on August 10. It featured the title track, “Lava Lamps” (featuring Beekwilder) and “Porn Star”.

Noyes left Lava Records shortly after the EP’s release, signing to MITS Records in 2019. The singles “Love Don’t Cost a Thang” and “Sunlight” precede her long-awaited debut album, due for release later this year.

songs.title: ​in my miNd

description.plain:
“In My Mind” is the debut single for https://genius.com/artists/Maty-noyes, who has previously appeared on  The Weeknd’s “Angel” and Kygo’s “Stay.”

On “In My Mind,” the Mississippi-born, Nashville-bred, and LA-based singer-songwriter sings about the complexities of love. She told Genius that she wrote the song based on her experience dating her boyfriend—the same relationship she sings about on “Stay.”

songs.title: Say It To My Face

description.plain:
“Say It To My Face” is the fifth single from American singer-songwriter Maty Noyes. At the time, it was expected to be the lead single from her anticipated debut album.

The song entails a relationship where it all feels too right. Maty wants mistakes, she wants a mess. She wants to really know her partner rather than him be picture-perfect.

songs.title: New Friends

description.plain:
“New Friends” is the 4th track on Maty Noyes' second extended play, Love Songs From a Lolita. It was released as an EP track on August 10th, 2018.

The song was first teased on Noyes' Instagram, where she posted an animated teaser for the song, stating:

New friends : a song about a lot of close friends letting me down, when I wrote this song I was in the thick of it. It’s throwing major shade but it serves friendship realness.

A music video for the song was first teased at the beginning of 2019 on her Instagram (as well as on her Twitter).

A few weeks later, a music video teaser was posted on her Instagram (and Twitter) along with the release date of the video, which was later pushed back. The video shows Noyes taking cupcakes from the oven, and icing them with a special liquid, perceivably poison. She places them in the fridge with a written sign stating to not eat them.

The music video was eventually released on February 19th, 2019 on Noyes' channel. The video was written and directed by Ian Rowe.
